abstract: Mr. Biden said his words about Southern segregationists who served with him in the Senate were misunderstood and stopped just short of an apology.
snippet: Mr. Biden said his words about Southern segregationists who served with him in the Senate were misunderstood and stopped just short of an apology.
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Saturday sought to tamp down anger over his praise for the bygone civility of a Senate that included notorious segregationists, stopping just short of an apology while asserting that his reference to never being called “boy” by one of the senators was not racial in nature.

abstract: I have written almost 450 postcards to politicians. As Margaret Atwood said, “A word after a word after a word is power.”
snippet: I have written almost 450 postcards to politicians. As Margaret Atwood said, “A word after a word after a word is power.”
lead_paragraph: MONTCLAIR, N.J. — My routine is the same every morning: I wake up, pour a cup of coffee and write to the president — or occasionally, to another politician. This month, I’ll mail my 450th postcard to Washington.

abstract: Can his rivals fracture or overwhelm his coalition?
snippet: Can his rivals fracture or overwhelm his coalition?
lead_paragraph: Where politicians are concerned, especially aging and garrulous ones, it may be a mistake to attribute to strategy what can be chalked up to simple fecklessness. But amid the shambolic style of Joe Biden’s front-running campaign to date, the flip-flops and apparent gaffes, it’s possible to discern a certain method, a general plan for how the candidate hopes to run for president: by changing positions on issues when he needs to, but without betraying his own amour-propre, his sense of what being Joe Biden is supposed to mean.

abstract: Though many African-Americans in South Carolina have favored Joseph R. Biden Jr. they are taking a hard look at several other candidates and considering all issues, not just race.
snippet: Though many African-Americans in South Carolina have favored Joseph R. Biden Jr. they are taking a hard look at several other candidates and considering all issues, not just race.
lead_paragraph: McCLELLANVILLE, S.C. — Joseph R. Biden Jr. enjoys a sizable advantage with black voters in South Carolina right now, and not just at lunch tables where they discuss candidates over freshly caught shrimp and fried fish. Recent polls have shown him with support from about 50 percent of African-American voters in the state.

abstract: We spent three months putting the 2020 Democrats on the spot. We were skeptical that most of them would participate. Here’s what it was like.

snippet: In her forthcoming book “What Do We Need Men For?,” the Elle advice columnist says the president assaulted her in the 1990s.
lead_paragraph: The advice columnist E. Jean Carroll accused President Trump of sexually assaulting her in the mid-1990s in her forthcoming book.

abstract: Many of Joe Biden’s views that are currently drawing criticism have been evident for years. But they are now provoking an entirely different response.
snippet: Many of Joe Biden’s views that are currently drawing criticism have been evident for years. But they are now provoking an entirely different response.
lead_paragraph: Joseph R. Biden Jr. was addressing an elite audience, describing how as a young senator he had learned to work with Jesse Helms, the right-wing North Carolinian known for his fierce opposition to civil rights and his open loathing of gay people. He once believed Mr. Helms had “no redeeming social value,” Mr. Biden said, until a senior Democratic senator chided him, explaining that Mr. Helms and his wife had adopted a disabled teenager.

abstract: Mr. Weissmann appears to be the first prosecutor on the special counsel’s team to agree to write a book, though it is not clear how much he will reveal.
snippet: Mr. Weissmann appears to be the first prosecutor on the special counsel’s team to agree to write a book, though it is not clear how much he will reveal.
lead_paragraph: Andrew Weissmann, one of the top prosecutors for Robert S. Mueller III on the Russia investigation, is writing a book that will explore his work on the special counsel’s inquiry, according to a publishing executive with knowledge of the deal.
